{"title_page": "Carmen Ferrer", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Carme Ferrer\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Carmen Ferrer Tatay\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|11|10}}\n| birth_place    = [[Valencia, Spain|Valencia]], [[Spain]]\n| height         = {{convert|1.66|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| currentclub    = \n| position       = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    =\n| youthclubs1    =\n| years1         = 2005\u20132007\n| years2         = 2007\u20132010\n| clubs1         = [[Levante UD (women)|Levante UD \"B\"]]\n| clubs2         = [[Valencia CF (women)|Valencia CF]]\n| caps1          =\n| caps2          = \n| goals1         = \n| goals2         = \n| nationalyears1 =  \n| nationalteam1  = \n| nationalcaps1  = \n| nationalgoals1 =\n}}\n'''Carmen Ferrer Tatay''' (born 10 November 1986), commonly known as '''Carme''', is a Spanish former [[Association football|football]] [[midfielder]], who played in Spain's [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n (women)|Superliga Femenina]] for [[Levante UD (women)|Levante UD]]<ref>[https://archive.is/20120716035924/http://usuarios.multimania.es/levantefemenino/pb.htm 2006-07 Levante squad] in Levante UDF's non official web</ref> and [[Valencia CF (women)|Valencia CF]].<ref>[http://www.anuariodeldeportevalenciano.com/2009/html/09/07/a01.php Providencial reacci\u00f3n final] Anuario del Deporte Valenciano</ref>\n\nShe was a member of the [[Spain women's national football team|Under-19 Spanish team]] that won the [[2004 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship|2004 U-19 European Championship]]<ref>[http://hemeroteca.mundodeportivo.com/preview/2004/08/09/pagina-29/774319/pdf.html?search=dieguez Las chicas tambi\u00e9n son guerreras] [[El Mundo Deportivo]]</ref> and took part in the [[2004 FIFA U-19 Women's World Championship|2004 U-20 World Cup]].<ref>[http://es.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/tournament=108/edition=8311/matches/match=83110017/report.html Line-ups]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111108133045/http://es.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/tournament%3D108/edition%3D8311/matches/match%3D83110017/report.html |date=November 8, 2011 }} of the 2004 U20 WC's USA-Spain in [[FIFA]].com</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===International===\n; Spain\n* [[UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship]] (1): [[2004 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship|2004]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferrer, Carmen}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Spanish women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Primera Divisi\u00f3n (women) players]]\n[[Category:Levante UD Femenino players]]\n[[Category:Valencia CF Femenino players]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Valencia (city)]]\n[[Category:Women's association football midfielders]]\n{{Spain-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Carme Ferrer\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Carmen Ferrer Tatay\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|11|10}}\n| birth_place    = [[Valencia, Spain|Valencia]], [[Spain]]\n| height         = {{convert|1.66|m|ftin|abbr=on}}\n| currentclub    = \n| position       = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    =\n| youthclubs1    =\n| years1         = 2005\u20132007\n| years2         = 2007\u20132010\n| clubs1         = [[Levante UD (women)|Levante UD \"B\"]]\n| clubs2         = [[Valencia CF (women)|Valencia CF]]\n| caps1          =\n| caps2          = \n| goals1         = \n| goals2         = \n| nationalyears1 =  \n| nationalteam1  = \n| nationalcaps1  = \n| nationalgoals1 =\n}}\n'''Carmen Ferrer Tatay''' (born 10 November 1986), commonly known as '''Carme''', is a Spanish former [[Association football|football]] [[midfielder]], who played in Spain's [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n (women)|Superliga Femenina]] for [[Levante UD (women)|Levante UD]]<ref>[https://archive.is/20120716035924/htt