{"title_page": "WWE Universal Championship", "text_new": "\n\n{{short description|Championship created and promoted by the American professional wrestling promotion WWE}}\n{{Distinguish|WWE Championship|World Heavyweight Championship (WWE)}}\n{{pp-protected|reason=Persistent [[WP:Disruptive editing|disruptive editing]] Enough.|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox pro wrestling championship\n|name          = WWE Universal Championship\n|image         = [[file:Universal Championship.png|240px]]\n|caption       = The current Universal Championship belt with default side plates<br>(2019\u2013present)<br>\n|promotion     = [[WWE]]\n|brand         = [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]<!-- BRANDS ARE NOT ITALICIZED, JUST TV SHOWS. -->\n|currentholder = [[Braun Strowman]]\n|won = March 25 or 26, 2020\n|aired = April 4, 2020\n|created       = July 25, 2016\n|firstchamp    = [[Finn B\u00e1lor]]\n|mostreigns    = [[Brock Lesnar]] (3 reigns)\n|longestreign  = [[Brock Lesnar]] (504 days{{efn|Despite initially recognizing this number, the WWE recognize the reign as having lasted 503 days.}})\n|shortestreign = [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] (22 Hours)\n|oldest        = [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]] ({{age in years and days|1966|12|27|2020|02|27}})\n|youngest      = [[Kevin Owens]] ({{age in years and days|1984|05|07|2016|08|29}})\n|heaviest      = [[Braun Strowman]] ({{Convert|385|lb|kg|abbr=on}}) <!--The Fiend was introduced as 290 pounds during his title match in Saudi Arabia -->\n|lightest      = [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] ({{Convert|190|lb|kg|abbr=on}}) \n}}\n\nThe '''WWE Universal Championship''' is a [[Professional wrestling championship#World championships|world heavyweight championship]]{{#tag:ref|[[WWE]] has referred to the Universal Championship as a \"world title\", both on its programming<ref>{{cite episode|title=[[SummerSlam (2016)]] (Finn B\u00e1lor vs. Seth Rollins for the Universal Championship)|series=''[[SummerSlam]]''|network=[[WWE Network]]|date=August 21, 2016|minutes=200|quote=Finn B\u00e1lor becomes the first Superstar to ever win a world title in his debut match on a pay-per-view.}}</ref> and in print.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/article/roman-reigns-brock-lesnar-insults-analyzed|title=Breaking down five insults from Reigns' verbal attack on Lesnar|quote=Universal Champion Brock Lesnar... is the franchise player of the moment. He's Raw's reigning World Title holder.|last=Benigno|first=Anthony|date=March 3, 2018|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=May 31, 2018}}</ref> This designation has been corroborated by [[WP:PW/RS|reliable sources]] such as ''Pro Wrestling Dot Net'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prowrestling.net/site/2016/07/25/725-powells-wwe-raw-live-tv-review-the-brand-split-begins-new-broadcast-team-night-after-wwe-battleground-finn-balor-debut/|title=7/25 Powell's WWE Raw Live TV Review: New World Title, the brand split begins, Finn Balor and Nia Jax debut|last=Powell|first=Jason|date=July 25, 2016|publisher=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|access-date=July 30, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Wade Keller#Pro Wrestling Torch|Pro Wrestling Torch]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/08/09/instant-reaction-88-raw-first-batch-pwtorch-writers-reviewing-mondays-raw/|title=8/8 Raw|last=Tucker|first=Ben|date=August 9, 2016|website=[[Wade Keller#Pro Wrestling Torch|Pro Wrestling Torch]]|access-date=June 1, 2018}}</ref> [[ESPN]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/wwe/story/_/id/17416755/kevin-owens-wins-wwe-universal-championship-elimination-match-raw|title=Kevin Owens wins WWE Universal Championship in Fatal 4-way elimination match|last=Fiorvanti|first=Tim|date=August 30, 2016|publisher=[[ESPN]]|access-date=June 1, 2018}}</ref> [[Fox Sports]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/wwe/gallery/list-of-wwe-champions-john-cena-title-drought-kevin-owens-seth-rollins-roman-reigns-083116|title=8 WWE stars that have won a World Championship more recently than John Cena|last=Schwartz|first=Nick|date=October 20, 2016|publisher=[[Fox Sports]]|access-date=June 1, 2018}}</ref> [[Sky Sports]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/wwe/news/14203/10513013/wwe-raw-finn-balor-earns-world-title-shot-with-big-win-on-raw-debut|title=WWE Raw: Finn Balor earns world title shot with big win on Raw debut|last=Ruse|first=David|date=July 26, 2016|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|accessdate=July 30, 2016}}</ref> and [[Canoe.com|Slam! Sports]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/PPVReports/2017/06/28/22734486.html|title=Countdown to Great Balls of Fire|last=Hillhouse|first=David|date=June 28, 2017|publisher=[[Canoe.com|Slam! Sports]]|access-date=June 1, 2018}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha}} created and promoted by the [[United States|American]] [[professional wrestling promotion]] [[WWE]], currently defended on their [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown brand]]. It is one of three world titles in WWE, alongside the [[WWE Championship]] on [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and the [[NXT Championship]] on [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]]. The current champion is [[Braun Strowman]], who is in his first reign.\n\nNamed in honor of the [[WWE#Terminology|WWE Universe]], the championship was established on July 25, 2016 to be the top title of the Raw brand. Its creation came as a result of the re-introduction of the [[WWE brand extension|brand split]] and subsequent [[2016 WWE draft|draft]] on July 19, 2016 in which the WWE Championship, the promotion's original world title, became exclusive to SmackDown. The inaugural Universal Champion was [[Finn B\u00e1lor]]. Since its inception, matches for the championship have headlined several [[List of WWE pay-per-view events|pay-per-view events]], including [[SummerSlam (2017)|SummerSlam in 2017]],<ref name=\"SSlam2017\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=Powell's WWE SummerSlam 2017 live review: Brock Lesnar vs. Braun Strowman vs. Samoa Joe vs. Roman Reigns for the WWE Universal Championship, Jinder Mahal vs. Shinsuke Nakamura for the WWE Championship, Sheamus and Cesaro vs. Dean Ambrose and Seth Rollins for the Raw Tag Titles|url=http://prowrestling.net/site/2017/08/20/powells-wwe-summerslam-2017-live-review-brock-lesnar-vs-braun-strowman-vs-samoa-joe-vs-roman-reigns-wwe-universal-championship-jinder-mahal-vs-shinsuke-nakamura-wwe-champio/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=August 20, 2017|date=2017-08-20}}</ref> [[SummerSlam (2018)|2018]],<ref name=\"SSlam2018\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=Powell's WWE SummerSlam 2018 live review: Brock Lesnar vs. Roman Reigns for the WWE Universal Championship, AJ Styles vs. Samoa Joe for the WWE Championship, Alexa Bliss vs. Ronda Rousey for the Raw Women's Championship, Daniel Bryan vs. The Miz|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2018/08/19/powells-wwe-summerslam-2018-live-review-brock-lesnar-vs-roman-reigns-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-aj-styles-vs-samoa-joe-for-the-wwe-championship-alexa-bliss-vs-ronda-rousey-for-the-raw/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=August 19, 2018|date=2018-08-19}}</ref> [[SummerSlam (2019)|2019]],<ref name=\"SSlam2019\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE SummerSlam results: Powell's live review of Brock Lesnar vs. Seth Rollins for the WWE Universal Championship, Kofi Kingston vs. Samoa Randy Orton for the WWE Championship, Kevin Owens vs. Shane McMahon, Trish Stratus vs. Charlotte Flair, \"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt vs. Finn Balor|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/08/11/wwe-summerslam-results-powells-live-review-of-brock-lesnar-vs-seth-rollins-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-kofi-kingston-vs-samoa-randy-orton-for-the-wwe-championship-kevin-owens-vs-shane-m/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=August 11, 2019|date=2019-08-11}}</ref> and [[WrestleMania 34]],<ref name=\"WM34\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=Powell's WrestleMania 34 live review: AJ Styles vs. Shinsuke Nakamura for the WWE Championship, Brock Lesnar vs. Roman Reigns for the WWE Universal Championship, Charlotte Flair vs. Asuka for the Smackdown Women's Championship, Ronda Rousey and Kurt Angle vs. Triple H and Stephanie McMahon|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2018/04/08/powells-wrestlemania-34-live-review-aj-styles-vs-shinsuke-nakamura-for-the-wwe-championship-brock-lesnar-vs-roman-reigns-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-charlotte-flair-vs-as/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|accessdate=April 8, 2018|date=2018-04-08}}</ref> both being two of WWE's \"big four\" pay-per-views, the latter of which is WWE's flagship event. \n\nThe title was one of two world titles in the promotion until the NXT Championship's recognition in 2017 as well as NXT becoming a main brand in 2019. Following the events of [[Crown Jewel (2019)|Crown Jewel 2019]], the Universal and WWE Championships switched brands.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:NXT Champion Finn Balor 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|The inaugural champion [[Finn B\u00e1lor]], shown here as his \"Demon\" persona, which he used to win the championship]]\nIn mid-2016, the [[WWE]] reintroduced the [[WWE brand extension|brand extension]], where the promotion split its main roster between their [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] and [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] brands, represented by the shows of the same name (the previous brand extension ended in 2011).<ref>{{cite magazine|title=WWE's 'Smackdown' Will Move To Live Broadcast On USA (Exclusive)|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/wwe-smackdown-live-usa-1201782569/|last=Steinberg|first=Brian|date=May 25, 2016|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=May 25, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WWE's destiny to be determined during SmackDown's Live premiere|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/article/live-draft-smackdown-premiere?sf29076738|publisher=WWE|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref> On July 19, 2016, ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]'' began [[Live television|broadcasting live]] and on that premiere of ''SmackDown Live'', the [[2016 WWE Draft]] took place and reigning [[WWE Championship|WWE Champion]] [[Dean Ambrose]] was drafted to SmackDown.<ref name=\"Draft\">{{cite web|title=2016 WWE Draft results: WWE officially ushers in New Era|url=http://www.wwe.com/2016-wwe-draft-results|publisher=WWE|accessdate=July 19, 2016}}</ref> At [[Battleground (2016)|Battleground]] on July 24, Ambrose retained the title in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple threat match]] against Raw draftees [[Seth Rollins]] and [[Roman Reigns]],<ref name=\"BG16\">{{cite web|last=Caldwell|first=James|title=7/24 WWE Battleground Results \u2013 CALDWELL'S Complete Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/07/24/jcbattlegroundppvreport/|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=July 24, 2016|accessdate=July 24, 2016}}</ref> leaving Raw without a [[Professional wrestling championship#World championships|world championship]].<ref name=\"BGShield\">{{cite web|last1=Melok|first1=Bobby|title=WWE Champion Dean Ambrose def. Roman Reigns & Seth Rollins (Triple Threat Match)|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwebattleground/2016/dean-ambrose-seth-rollins-roman-reigns-triple-threat-results|publisher=WWE|accessdate=July 24, 2016}}</ref> On the following episode of ''[[WWE Raw|Monday Night Raw]]'', the brand's Commissioner [[Stephanie McMahon]] and General Manager [[Mick Foley]] created the WWE Universal Championship to serve as the brand's top championship. The title was named in honor of the WWE Universe, the name the promotion uses to refer to its fan base.<ref name=\"Raw07252016\">{{cite web|last1=Tedesco|first1=Mike|title=WWE RAW Results \u2013 7/25/16 (Live from Pittsburgh, fallout from Battleground, new era of RAW begins)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-wrestling-results/wwe-raw-results/64911-wwe-raw-results-72516-live-pittsburgh-fallout-battleground-new-era-raw-begins/|work=Wrestleview|date=July 25, 2016|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe inaugural champion was crowned at [[SummerSlam (2016)|SummerSlam]] on August 21 in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Variations of singles matches|pinfall and submission-only singles match]]. Seth Rollins was automatically set for that match as he was Raw's number one draft pick and was not pinned in the WWE Championship match at Battleground. His opponent was determined by two [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|fatal four-way matches]] on ''Raw'', with the winners wrestling each other in a singles match.<ref name=\"Raw07252016\"/> [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] won the first fatal four-way by defeating [[Cesaro (wrestler)|Cesaro]], [[Kevin Owens]], and [[Rusev (wrestler)|Rusev]] while Roman Reigns won the second by defeating [[Chris Jericho]], [[Sami Zayn]], and [[Sheamus]].<ref name=\"Raw07252016\"/> B\u00e1lor then defeated Reigns and was added to the title match.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Clapp|first1=John|title=Finn B\u00e1lor vs. Seth Rollins to crown the first WWE Universal Champion|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/summerslam/2016/finn-balor-seth-rollins-universal-championship|work=WWE|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> At SummerSlam, B\u00e1lor defeated Rollins to become the inaugural champion. B\u00e1lor was the first WWE wrestler to win a world title in his [[List of WWE pay-per-view events|pay-per-view]] debut as well as winning his first world title in less than a month of his debut on [[List of WWE personnel#Main roster|WWE's main roster]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Laboon|first1=Jeff|title=Finn B\u00e1lor def. Seth Rollins|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/summerslam/2016/wwe-universal-championship-finn-balor-seth-rollins-result|work=WWE|accessdate=August 21, 2016}}</ref> During the championship match, however, B\u00e1lor suffered a legitimate shoulder injury and was forced to vacate the title the following day.<ref name=\"Vacancy\"/><ref name=\"Raw08222016\"/>\n\nIn 2017, the [[NXT Championship]] was recognized as a world title, thus having three world championships in the WWE,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/titlehistory/nxt-championship|title=NXT Championship|work=[[WWE]].com|quote=Fulfilling a prophecy first laid out by WWE Chairman [[Mr. McMahon]] years earlier, [[Drew McIntyre]] captured a world championship in a WWE ring when he defeated [[Bobby Roode]] to claim the NXT Title at [[TakeOver: Brooklyn III]]}}</ref> though the [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] brand itself did not become the promotion's third major brand until September 2019 when it was moved to the [[USA Network]]; the brand was formerly a [[Farm team|developmental territory]] for WWE.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/wrestling/triple-h-discusses-nxt-as-a-third-brand-putting-talent-in-a-position-to-succeed-more/|title=Triple H Discusses NXT as a Third Brand, Putting Talent in a Position to Succeed, More \u2013 411MANIA|website=www.411mania.com}}</ref> At [[Crown Jewel (2019)|Crown Jewel]] on October 31, 2019, SmackDown wrestler [[\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt]] won the Universal title by defeating Seth Rollins in a [[Falls Count Anywhere match]] that could not be stopped for any reason, thus transferring the Universal Championship to SmackDown.<ref>{{cite web|last=Benigno|first=Anthony|title=\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt def. Seth Rollins to become the new Universal Champion (Falls Count Anywhere Match)|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/wwe-crown-jewel/2019/seth-rollins-vs-the-fiend-bray-wyatt-results|work=WWE|date=October 31, 2019|accessdate=November 1, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"CrownJewel2019\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=WWE Crown Jewel results: Powell's live review of Brock Lesnar vs. Cain Velasquez for the WWE Championship, Seth Rollins vs. Bray Wyatt in a Falls Count Anywhere match for the WWE Universal Championship, Braun Strowman vs. Tyson Fury, Lacey Evans vs. Natalya|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/10/31/wwe-crown-jewel-results-powells-live-review-of-brock-lesnar-vs-cain-velasquez-for-the-wwe-championship-seth-rollins-vs-bray-wyatt-in-a-falls-count-anywhere-match-for-the-wwe-universal-championsh/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=October 31, 2019|date=2019-10-31}}</ref> The WWE Championship was subsequently transferred to Raw after reigning champion [[Brock Lesnar]] quit SmackDown the following day, taking the title to Raw.<ref name=\"SmackDown10042019\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=10/04 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell's review of The Rock's return, Kofi Kingston vs. Brock Lesnar for the WWE Championship, Kevin Owens vs. Shane McMahon in a career vs. career ladder match, Becky Lynch and Charlotte Flair vs. Sasha Banks and Bayley|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/10/04/10-04-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-the-rocks-return-kofi-kingston-vs-brock-lesnar-for-the-wwe-championship-kevin-owens-vs-shane-mcmahon-in-a-career-vs-career-ladder-m/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|date=October 4, 2019|accessdate=October 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Brand designation ==\nThe following is a list of dates indicating the transitions of the WWE Universal Championship between the Raw and SmackDown brands.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%; text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Date of transition || Brand || Notes\n|-\n|-\n|July 25, 2016\n|style=\"background:#fbb;\"|[[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]]\n|The championship was established for [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] after [[WWE Champion]] [[Dean Ambrose]] was drafted to [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] in the [[2016 WWE Draft]]. [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] subsequently became the inaugural Universal Champion at [[SummerSlam (2016)|SummerSlam]] on August 21.\n|-\n|October 31, 2019\n|style=\"background:#bbf;\"|[[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]]\n|The Universal Championship moved to [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] after [[\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt]], a member of the SmackDown brand, defeated [[Seth Rollins]] in a [[Falls Count Anywhere match]] that could not be stopped for any reason to win the Universal Championship.\n|}\n\n== Championship belt design ==\nThe Universal Championship belt is similar in appearance to the WWE Championship belt ([[WWE Championship#Current design|introduced in 2014]]), with a few notable differences. Like the WWE Championship belt, the center plate is a large cut out of the WWE logo with diamonds sitting inside an irregular heptagonal plate, but with the capital words \"Universal Champion\" in small print sitting underneath the logo. Just the same, there are gold divider bars that separate the center plate from its two side plates. Each side plate features the same default removable center section as the WWE Championship (the WWE logo over a red globe), which can be customized with the champion's logo.<ref name=\"originaldesign\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/summerslam/2016/gallery/wwe-universal-championship-photos#fid-40044827|title=An up-close look at the all-new WWE Universal Championship: photos|publisher=[[WWE]]|date=August 21, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref> The most prominent difference is the belt's strap, the color of which indicates the brand it is exclusive to. When the belt was first unveiled at SummerSlam 2016, the strap was red to symbolize its exclusivity to the Raw brand, and the underline of the WWE logo on the center plate was black to make it visible (essentially the reverse of the WWE Championship belt).<ref name=\"originaldesign\"/> After the title became exclusive to SmackDown in late 2019, Bray Wyatt introduced a blue strap variation and the underline of the WWE logo was changed from black to red.<ref name=\"SmackDown11152019\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/11/15/11-15-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-big-e-and-kofi-kingston-vs-the-revival-for-the-smackdown-tag-titles-daniel-bryan-on-miz-tv-bayley-vs-nikki-cross-mustafa-ali-and-shor/|title=11/15 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell's review of Big E and Kofi Kingston vs. The Revival for the Smackdown Tag Titles, Daniel Bryan on Miz TV, Bayley vs. Nikki Cross, Mustafa Ali and Shorty G put their Team Smackdown spots on the line vs. Robert Roode and Dolph Ziggler|date=November 15, 2019|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=November 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/gallery/new-look-universal-title-the-fiend-bray-wyatt#fid-40400419|title=Universal Title turns blue with \"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt's reign: photos|work=[[WWE]].com|accessdate=November 17, 2019}}</ref> \n\nIn addition to the SmackDown version of the belt, Wyatt also introduced a custom version of the championship for his \"Fiend\" character on the November 29 episode of ''SmackDown''.<ref name=\"SmackDown11292019\">{{cite web|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/11/29/11-29-wwe-friday-night-smackdown-results-powells-review-of-a-new-face-in-bray-wyatts-firefly-funhouse-new-days-open-challenge-for-a-smackdown-tag-title-match-roman-reigns-opening-the-show/|title=11/29 WWE Friday Night Smackdown results: Powell's review of a new face in Bray Wyatt's Firefly Funhouse, New Day's open challenge for a Smackdown Tag Title match, Roman Reigns opening the show|date=November 29, 2019|last=Powell|first=Jason|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=November 30, 2019}}</ref> The custom belt featured The Fiend's face in the place of the center plate. The character's phrases \"Hurt\" and \"Heal\" were written in red on black leather strips in the place of side plates while the strap of the belt itself was red and black worn leather with red stitching holding it together. The character's phrase \"Let Me In\" were also included; the far left side of the strap said \"LET\" in red, \"ME\" was represented by The Fiend's face at the center, and the far right side said \"IN\" in red. Wyatt used both the standard and custom versions of the championship; his cheery Firefly Fun House character held the standard blue belt, while his sinister Fiend character held the custom belt.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/article/bray-wyatt-reveals-new-look-universal-title|title=Bray Wyatt unveils a dark and twisted Universal Title|date=November 29, 2019|work=[[WWE]]|accessdate=November 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/gallery/bray-wyatt-unveils-haunting-new-title#fid-40403879|title=\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt's dark and twisted Universal Title: photos|date=November 29, 2019|work=[[WWE]]|accessdate=November 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Reception ===\nThe Universal Championship design was heavily criticized.<ref name=\"vorel\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/10/ranking-every-current-wwe-title-belt-from-best-to.html|title=Ranking Every Current WWE Title Belt, From Best to Worst|last=Vorel|first=Jim|date=October 10, 2016|website=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|access-date=February 14, 2017|quote=The most recent WWE world title, exclusive to Raw, has had a lot of shit thrown at it.}}</ref> Jason Powell of ''Pro Wrestling Dot Net'' referred to it as \"a title belt that no one likes\".<ref name=\"dot net\">{{cite web|url=http://prowrestling.net/site/2016/08/22/822-powells-wwe-raw-live-tv-review-finn-balor-injury-and-the-wwe-universal-championship-summerslam-fallout/|title= 8/22 Powell's WWE Raw Live TV Review: Finn Balor injury and the WWE Universal Championship, SummerSlam fallout|last=Powell|first=Jason|date=August 22, 2016|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|access-date=August 23, 2016}}</ref> Adam Silverstein of [[CBS Sports]] described it as \"ugly\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/general/news/wwe-summerslam-2016-results-live-blog-matches-highlights-updates/|title=WWE SummerSlam 2016 results: Brock Lesnar gets savage, Finn Balor wins title|last=Silverstein|first=Adam|date=August 21, 2016|publisher=[[CBS Sports]]|access-date=August 21, 2016}}</ref> while the live SummerSlam audience in [[Brooklyn, New York]] gave derisive chants, including \"This belt sucks\",<ref name=\"meltzer082116\">{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/wwe-summerslam-live-results-brock-lesnar-vs-randy-orton-218311 |title=WWE SummerSlam live results: Brock Lesnar vs. Randy Orton |last=Meltzer |first=Dave |date=August 21, 2016 |website=Wrestling Observer |access-date=August 21, 2016 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160822045012/http://www.f4wonline.com/wwe-news/wwe-summerslam-live-results-brock-lesnar-vs-randy-orton-218311 |archivedate=August 22, 2016 }}</ref> an assessment with which [[New England Sports Network]] reporters agreed.<ref>http://nesn.com/2016/08/wwe-summerslam-2016-live-results-highlights-from-every-match-in-brooklyn/</ref> That site's Ricky Doyle wrote that the crowd response turned what should have been a \"landmark moment for the company\" into an \"awkward experience\".<ref name=\"nesn\"/> Mike Johnson of ''Pro Wrestling Insider'' felt the title looked like a \"xerox\" of the WWE Championship and did not blame the audience for reacting negatively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/ViewArticle.php?id=104220&p=2|title=What happened after SummerSlam went off the air and more|last=Johnson|first=Mike|date=August 21, 2016|website=PWInsider|access-date=February 14, 2017}}</ref> The design was also unpopular with online wrestling fans.<ref name=\"meltzer082116\"/>\n\nWWE employees responded in the aftermath of the title's debut. Seth Rollins chastised the SummerSlam crowd's reaction, writing on [[Twitter]]: \"More important than a title's appearance is what it represents for the men fighting over it. You really let me down tonight, Brooklyn.\"<ref name=\"nesn\">{{cite web|url=http://nesn.com/2016/08/seth-rollins-rips-brooklyn-barclays-center-crowd-after-wwe-summerslam/|title=Seth Rollins Rips Barclays Center Crowd After WWE SummerSlam Reaction|last=Doyle|first=Ricky|date=August 22, 2016|publisher=[[New England Sports Network]]|access-date=August 23, 2016}}</ref> While acknowledging that he himself might have chosen a different belt design, Mick Foley echoed Rollins's response in a lengthy Facebook post. He recalled being presented with the [[WWE Hardcore Championship|WWF Hardcore Championship]], a title belt made of broken metal pieces held together by [[duct tape]], which challengers \"made [...] mean something by busting [their] asses\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxsports.com/wwe/story/mick-foley-rips-wwe-fans-for-their-reaction-at-summerslam-082216|title=Mick Foley laces WWE fans for their reaction at SummerSlam|last=Werner|first=Barry|date=August 22, 2016|publisher=Fox Sports|access-date=August 23, 2016}}</ref> In a [[kayfabe]] [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Promo|promo]] on the following episode of ''Raw'', the then-[[Heel (professional wrestling)|villainous]] Rollins called the championship belt \"beautiful\".<ref name=\"dot net\"/>\n\nLater in 2016, Jim Vorel of ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'' ranked the title as the worst of nine then contested in WWE, noting its \"obnoxious\" design.<ref name=\"vorel\"/> On the other hand, Nick Schwartz of [[Fox Sports]] wrote: \"It's really not as bad as fans made it seem at SummerSlam. It's fine.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.foxsports.com/wwe/gallery/wwe-championship-belt-ranking-best-121516 | title=The best and worst looking WWE Championship belts}}</ref>\n\n== Reigns ==\n[[File:Braun_March_2018.jpg|alt=|thumb|150px|Current champion [[Braun Strowman]]]]\nAs of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTDAY}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}, there have been twelve reigns between eight champions and two vacancies. Finn B\u00e1lor was the inaugural champion. Brock Lesnar holds three records with the championship: he has the most reigns at three, his first reign is the longest reign at 504 days (beginning on April 2, 2017 and ending on August 19, 2018), and he has the longest combined reign at 688 days (WWE recognizes 503 days and 686 days, respectively). B\u00e1lor has the shortest reign at 22 hours as he was forced to vacate the title due to suffering a [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Legit|legitimate]] injury in winning it. Kevin Owens is the youngest champion when he won it at {{age in years and days|1984|05|07|2016|08|29}} old<!--\"The Fiend\" Bray Wyatt was 32 years, 161 days old when he won the title.-->, while [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]] is the oldest when he won it at 53.\n\n[[Braun Strowman]] is the current champion in his first reign. He won the title by defeating [[Bill Goldberg|Goldberg]] during [[WrestleMania 36]] Part 1 that [[Broadcast delay|aired]] on April 4, 2020; the event was taped on March 25 and 26 in [[Orlando, Florida]], but it is currently unknown which day this match was taped.\n \n{{Professional wrestling title history top|active=yes|dayless=yes|unrecognized=yes|days2=yes}}\n{{PWtitlereign\n|sort number = 0.5\n|type = promotion\n|name = [[WWE]]: [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]]\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 1\n|champion = {{sortname|Finn|B\u00e1lor}}\n|reign    = 1\n|date     = {{dts|August 21, 2016}}\n|days     = <1\n|days2    = <1\n|location = [[Brooklyn, NY]]\n|event    = [[SummerSlam (2016)|SummerSlam]]\n|notes    = The title was established for [[Raw (WWE brand)|Raw]] after the [[WWE Championship]] became exclusive to [[SmackDown (WWE brand)|SmackDown]] following the [[2016 WWE Draft]]. B\u00e1lor defeated [[Seth Rollins]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Variations of singles matches|pinfall and submission-only match]] to become the inaugural champion.\n|ref      = <ref name=\"SSlam2016\">{{cite web|last=Caldwell|first=James|title=8/21 WWE Summerslam Results \u2013 Caldwell's Complete Live Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/08/21/summerslam2016resultsfinal/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 21, 2016}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|sort number = 1.5\n|type     = vacated\n|date     = {{dts|August 22, 2016}}\n|location = [[Brooklyn, NY]]\n|event    = ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]''\n|days2    = yes\n|notes    = Vacated due to [[Finn B\u00e1lor]] having a [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Legitimate|legit]] shoulder injury during his match at [[SummerSlam (2016)|SummerSlam]].\n|ref      = <ref name=\"Vacancy\">{{cite web|title=UPDATE: Finn B\u00e1lor relinquishes WWE Universal Championship due to injury, undergoes successful surgery|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2016-08-22/article/wwe-universal-champion-finn-balor-injured-at-summerslam|publisher=WWE|date=August 24, 2016|accessdate=August 24, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Raw08222016\">{{cite web|last1=Caldwell|first1=James|title=8/22 WWE Raw Results \u2013 CALDWELL'S Complete Live TV Report|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/08/22/aug22rawresultsfinal/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 22, 2016}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 2\n|champion = {{sortname|Kevin|Owens}}\n|reign    = 1\n|date     = {{dts|August 29, 2016}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|August 29, 2016|March 5, 2017}}\n|days2    = yes\n|location = [[Houston|Houston, TX]]\n|event    = ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]''\n|notes    = This was a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic elimination matches|fatal four-way elimination match]] for the vacant title also involving [[Big Cass]], [[Roman Reigns]], and [[Seth Rollins]].\n|ref      = <ref name=\"Raw08292016\">{{cite web|last1=Keller|first1=Wade|title=KELLER'S WWE RAW REVIEW 8/29: Ongoing coverage of fatal four way for the WWE Universal Title|url=http://www.pwtorch.com/site/2016/08/29/kellers-wwe-raw-review-829-ongoing-coverage-fatal-four-way-wwe-universal-title-match-kevin-owens-seth-rollins-roman-reigns-big-cass/|work=Pro Wrestling Torch|accessdate=August 29, 2016}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 3\n|champion = {{sortname||Goldberg|Bill Goldberg}}\n|reign    = 1\n|date     = {{dts|March 5, 2017}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|March 5, 2017|April 2, 2017}}\n|days2    = 27\n|location = [[Milwaukee|Milwaukee, WI]]\n|event    = [[Fastlane (2017)|Fastlane]]\n|notes    = \n|ref      = <ref name=\"Fastlane2017\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=3/5 Powell's WWE Fastlane Live Review: Kevin Owens vs. Goldberg for the WWE Championship, Roman Reigns vs. Braun Strowman, Bayley vs. Charlotte for the Raw Women's Championship, Samoa Joe vs. Sami Zayn|url=http://prowrestling.net/site/2017/03/05/35-powells-wwe-fastlane-live-review-kevin-owens-vs-goldberg-wwe-championship-roman-reigns-vs-braun-strowman-bayley-vs-charlotte-raw-womens-championship-samoa-joe-vs-sam/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|accessdate=March 5, 2017}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 4\n|champion = {{sortname|Brock|Lesnar}}\n|reign    = 1\n|date     = {{dts|April 2, 2017}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|April 2, 2017|August 19, 2018}}\n|days2    = 503\n|location = [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando, FL]]\n|event    = [[WrestleMania 33]]\n|notes    = \n|ref      = <ref name=\"WM33\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=Powell's WrestleMania 33 live review: Undertaker vs. Roman Reigns, Goldberg vs. Brock Lesnar for the WWE Universal Championship, AJ Styles vs. Shane McMahon, Seth Rollins vs. Triple H in an unsanctioned match|url=http://prowrestling.net/site/2017/04/02/powells-wrestlemania-33-live-review-undertaker-vs-roman-reigns-goldberg-vs-brock-lesnar-wwe-universal-championship-aj-styles-vs-shane-mcmahon-seth-rollins-vs-triple-h/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|accessdate=April 2, 2017|date=2017-04-02}}</ref>\n}}\n{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 5\n|champion = {{sortname|Roman|Reigns}}\n|reign    = 1\n|date     = {{dts|August 19, 2018}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|August 19, 2018|October 22, 2018}}\n|days2    = 63\n|location = [[Brooklyn, NY]]\n|event    = [[SummerSlam (2018)|SummerSlam]]\n|notes    = \n|ref      = <ref name=\"SSlam2018\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=Powell's WWE SummerSlam 2018 live review: Brock Lesnar vs. Roman Reigns for the WWE Universal Championship, AJ Styles vs. Samoa Joe for the WWE Championship, Alexa Bliss vs. Ronda Rousey for the Raw Women's Championship, Daniel Bryan vs. The Miz|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2018/08/19/powells-wwe-summerslam-2018-live-review-brock-lesnar-vs-roman-reigns-for-the-wwe-universal-championship-aj-styles-vs-samoa-joe-for-the-wwe-championship-alexa-bliss-vs-ronda-rousey-for-the-raw/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=August 19, 2018|date=2018-08-19}}</ref>\n}}{{PWtitlereign\n|sort number = 1.5\n|type     = vacated\n|date     = {{dts|October 22, 2018}}\n|location = [[Providence, RI]]\n|event    = ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]''\n|days2    = yes\n|notes    = Vacated after [[Roman Reigns]] announced that he had a legitimate diagnosis of [[leukemia]].\n|ref      = <ref>{{cite web|last=Benigno|first=Anthony|title=Roman Reigns relinquished the Universal Championship after revealing his battle with leukemia|url=https://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2018-10-22/article/roman-reigns-relinquished-universal-championship-leukemia-battle|publisher=WWE|accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Raw10222018\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=10/22 Powell's WWE Raw Live TV Review: Roman Reigns announces he has leukemia, forfeits the WWE Universal Championship, Drew McIntyre and Dolph Ziggler vs. Seth Rollins and Dean Ambrose for the Raw Tag Titles, Ronda Rousey and Nikki Bella contract signing for WWE Evolution, Triple H and Shawn Michaels appear|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2018/10/22/10-22-powells-wwe-raw-live-tv-review-drew-mcintyre-and-dolph-ziggler-vs-seth-rollins-and-dean-ambrose-for-the-raw-tag-titles-ronda-rousey-and-nikki-bella-contract-signing-for-wwe-evolution/|work=Pro Wreslting Dot Net|accessdate=October 22, 2018|date=2018-10-22}}</ref>\n}}\n{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 6\n|champion = {{sortname|Brock|Lesnar}}\n|reign    = 2\n|date     = {{dts|November 2, 2018}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|November 2, 2018|April 7, 2019}}\n|days2    = yes\n|location = [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]]\n|event    = [[Crown Jewel (2018)|Crown Jewel]]\n|notes    = Originally scheduled as a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|triple threat match]] in which [[Roman Reigns]] was to defend the WWE Universal Championship against Brock Lesnar and [[Braun Strowman]].<ref name=\"Raw09172018\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=9/17 Powell's WWE Raw Live TV Review: Undertaker responds to Triple H, fallout from WWE Hell in a Cell including Brock Lesnar interfering in the main event|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2018/09/17/9-17-powells-wwe-raw-live-tv-review-undertaker-responds-to-triple-h-fallout-from-wwe-hell-in-a-cell-including-brock-lesnar-interfering-in-the-main-event/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=September 17, 2018|date=2018-09-17}}</ref> After Reigns relinquished the WWE Universal Championship, the match became a singles match between Lesnar and Strowman for the vacant WWE Universal Championship.<ref name=\"Raw10222018\"/>\n|ref      = <ref name=\"CrownJewel\">{{cite web|last=Powell|first=Jason|title=Powell's WWE Crown Jewel live review: Brock Lesnar vs. Braun Strowman for the vacant WWE Universal Championship, AJ Styles vs. Samoa Joe for the WWE Championship, Undertaker and Kane vs. DX, World Cup tournament|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2018/11/02/powells-wwe-crown-jewel-live-review-brock-lesnar-vs-braun-strowman-for-the-vacant-wwe-universal-championship-aj-styles-vs-samoa-joe-for-the-wwe-championship-undertaker-and-kane-vs-dx-wor/|work=Pro Wrestling Dot Net|accessdate=November 2, 2018|date=2018-11-02}}</ref>\n}}\n{{PWtitlereign\n|number   = 7\n|champion = {{sortname|Seth|Rollins}}\n|reign    = 1\n|date     = {{dts|April 7, 2019}}\n|days     = {{age in days nts|April 7, 2019|July 14, 2019}}\n|days2    = yes\n|location = [[East Rutherford, NJ]]\n|event    = [[WrestleMania 35]]\n|notes    = \n|ref      = <ref name=\"WM35\">{{cite web|last1=Powell|first1=Jason|title=WrestleMania 35 results: Powell's live review of Ronda Rousey vs. Becky Lynch vs. Charlotte Flair for the Raw and Smackdown Women's Titles, Daniel Bryan vs. Kofi Kingston for the WWE Championship, Brock Lesnar vs. Seth Rollins for the WWE Universal Championship, Batista vs. Triple H, AJ Styles vs. Randy Orton|url=https://prowrestling.net/site/2019/04/07/wrestlemania-35-results-powells-live-r